A couple of days ago I went to Gokarna, a small but beautiful beach town in Karnataka. The town has a lot of small beaches which are connected by a trail.

My main purpose of visiting Gokarna was to go for that small beach trek.

We started late in the morning and it was very hot and humid by then. I even thought of canceling the trek but @shikha_maybe made sure we finish it that day itself.

And believe me you, it turned out to be one of the best treks I've done in a while.

Mai kaala ho kar ghar vapas aaya par us baat ka koi gum nahi. 

Don't believe me? Go check out for yourself. 
Or check the video link in bio 😁

We’ve normalized littering, ignoring overflowing bins, and blaming ‘the system’—but when do we start taking ownership?

This video isn’t about hate, it’s about hope.
Hope that we can unlearn bad habits and build a culture of respect, for places, people, and public spaces.
A cleaner India doesn’t start with policies. It starts with you and me.

Watch till the end. If it hits you, do one thing today:
Pick up that wrapper. Carry a trash bag. Message your local municipality.
Because traveling isn’t just about taking memories, it’s about leaving places better than you found them.

Here’s why it matters more than you think ⤵️

✅ A good stay sets the tone for your mornings and nights — the two moments when you’re most likely to reflect, recharge, and feel the impact of your travels.

✅ When your property has a view — city skyline, ocean, mountains — the vibe of your trip kicks in without even stepping out.

✅ You’re more likely to rest better, shoot better content, and feel like you’re on vacation when the surroundings match your dream destination.

For example:
📍KL: Rooftop pool with a view of all 3 iconic towers
📍Vietnam: Room opens straight into a private pool
📍Uttarakhand: Homestay facing the entire Himalayan range

You don’t need luxury — just intention while booking. Look for locations, views, and reviews that add emotion to your stay.

This simple tip can make even a budget trip feel premium.

This is for anyone who’s been craving an international experience but thought it was out of reach.

A 130-year-old Hindu temple…
A 140-feet tall golden Murugan statue…
And 272 colorful steps that lead you into a giant cave carved by time itself.

Batu Caves in Malaysia is a reminder of how far Indian culture has travelled and how deeply it’s rooted in the world.

I couldn’t believe something so grand, so spiritual, and so close to home exists outside India 🇮🇳🇲🇾
If you ever visit Malaysia—don’t miss this.
This one will stay with you.

Only 3 days. Only ₹10K. But the impact? Lifelong.
George Town, Malaysia isn’t just another destination—it’s where your love for travel deepens. From street art that tells stories to sunsets that feel like therapy, this place shifted something in me.

No visa needed. No overplanning. Just pack and go.
Because sometimes, the trip you think you can’t take… is the one you need the most.

🌏💭 Save up. Step out. Feel alive again.

Spend at least half a day at this Airport

I used to think airports were just transit points. But Changi Airport in Singapore completely changed that for me.
From the world-famous Rain Vortex to stunning skywalk views, mirror mazes, hedge mazes, cafes, and more — this place is an experience in itself.

💡 Tip: If you’re flying to Singapore, keep at least *half a day just to explore Changi. It deserves it.

✈️ This is now officially my favourite airport.
Would you spend your day here?👇

Not a single filter. Not a single edit.
This is exactly how the sky looked that day — dark orange and straight out of a dream.
